AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1074* House Bill No. 1096
by deleting SECTION 2 and substituting:
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 4-3-739(b)(1), is amended by adding
the following as new subdivisions:
(D) Enter into a community benefits agreement or any similar legal contract if the
agreement or contract imposes obligations or conditions on the employer regarding
employment practices, benefits, or operations that are not directly related to the
performance of the employer's duties under the economic development incentive;
(E) Commit a willful violation of a safety standard prescribed pursuant to the
Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1970 (9 U.S.C. ยง 651 et seq.) or the Occupational
Safety and Health Act of 1972, compiled in title 50, chapter 3, part 1, where the violation
causes the death of five (5) or more employees during the twelve (12) months preceding
the effective date of the incentive agreement or during the time the agreement is in
effect;
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting SECTION 3 and substituting:
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 4-3-739(d), is amended by adding
the following new subdivision:
(3) Subdivisions (b)(1)(D) and (b)(1)(E) apply to contracts, agreements, and
understandings executed, renewed, or otherwise modified on or after July 1, 2025.
SECTION 4. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
